mediaNotes: FISP was in a very dense stand of white pine saplings.

Singing from about 15-20 feet up in birch tree west of the goat barn at the edge of the field; I was standing under the other side of the same tree. After singing here, he flew to a perch on the electric fence north of the line of young pine trees and continued to sing, presumably being territorial. Recording started at 9:02 CDT. Dominant background species is a Kentucky Warbler; also House Wren, Tufted Titmouse, etc. Some wind interference; it was a rather breezy morning.
